{
  "function_path": "pandas/core/reshape/pivot.py",
  "function_name": "__internal_pivot_table",
  "justification": "This function implements the core pivot table computation for a single aggregation function. It is the internal workhorse called by the public pivot_table function after it splits list-valued aggregation arguments into individual calls. The function takes all required parameters (DataFrame, values, index, columns, aggfunc, fill_value, margins, dropna, margins_name, observed, sort, kwargs) and follows the exact procedure described: validates value labels and filters the DataFrame, groups data by concatenation of index and column keys, applies the aggregation function, drops all-NaN rows if dropna is set, unstacks column-key levels to create a 2D pivot layout, reindexes both axes against the full Cartesian product if dropna is false, sorts columns if requested, fills NaN values with integer downcasting for len aggregations, appends row/column totals if margins requested, and cleans up by dropping redundant column headers and transposing if necessary."
}

